# Marketing redesign (UI/UX Pro Max)

When changing **look-and-feel** of the public site, follow this workflow.  
For **product/content** decisions (portfolio, contact, legal, out-of-scope), see `70-marketing-product.mdc`.

## 1. Generate design system (required first step)

From repo root:

```powershell
python .cursor\skills\ui-ux-pro-max\scripts\search.py "portfolio personal brand senior full stack engineer system designer" --design-system -p "Yehuda Huri"
```

Use stack flag `--stack react` for MUI-specific guidance. Read `SKILL.md` for persist mode
(`design-system/yehuda-huri/MASTER.md`) once a direction is approved.

## 2. Map tokens into MUI theme

- Colors → `frontend/src/theme/theme.ts` and preset files under `frontend/src/theme/presets/`
- Typography → theme + Google Fonts in `index.html` if needed
- Spacing/sections → reuse `Section.tsx`, `AppLayout.tsx`, `sx-patterns.ts`

## 3. Single-page landing priorities

| Section | Goal |
|---------|------|
| Overview (hero) | Clear value prop, single "View my work" CTA, 3 feature cards |
| About / Experience | Credibility without résumé-style timeline |
| Skills | Scannable expertise, grouped by domain |
| Portfolio | Proof — sliding image gallery, tags, outbound links |

## 4. Pre-delivery checklist (from skill)

- Contrast ≥ 4.5:1 on text; visible focus states; skip-to-main link works
- No layout shift on load; responsive at 375 / 768 / 1024 / 1440
- RTL (he) must not break nav, hero, or form layout
- Dark mode parity — no hardcoded light-only backgrounds
- All new copy through i18n keys under `marketing.*` or `legal.*`

## 5. Do not

- Add one-off styled buttons outside MUI theme component overrides
- Hardcode marketing copy in JSX
- Re-introduce backend/auth/Firebase/Redux — this is a frontend-only site
- Re-introduce freelance/services/pricing framing (Services, FAQ, "hire me")
- Add testimonials, blog, newsletter, or phone CTAs without explicit user request
